    • Constructor Detail

      • HadoopJobRunner

        public HadoopJobRunner(Running client,
               org.apache.log4j.Logger log,
               int progressLookupInterval)
        Creates HadoopJobRunner instance with given client, log and progress lookup interval.
        Parameters:
        client - Running that tells if currently running job should continue to run.
        log - A log used to log progress of running jobs.
        progressLookupInterval - Interval in which progress of jobs run using this instance should be monitored and logged. Can be zero but not negative.

    • Method Detail

      • runJobLogProgress

        public final HadoopJobResult runJobLogProgress(HadoopMapReduceService mapRedService,
                                HadoopMapReduceJob job,
                                java.util.Properties additionalJobSettings,
                                boolean runAsDaemon)
        Runs Hadoop map/reduce job specified by parameter using given HadoopMapReduceService. This method blocs while the job is not complete (HadoopJobReporter.isComplete()), method Running.runIt() of the client given in constructor returns true and the job did not timeout. While the job is running its progress is logged. TODO Add support for asynchronous jobs. UPDATE very basic support added
        Parameters:
        mapRedService - Non null map/reduce service used to send job to Hadoop cluster.
        job - Non null specification of the job to be send and monitored.
        additionalJobSettings - Non null additional settings for the job to be sent provided by user.
        runAsDaemon - true if the job should not be killed after Running.runIt() returns false, false otherwise.
        Returns:
        Result containing locally measured info about the job and instance of HadoopJobReporter that provides access to on the cluster information about the job.
